To support evidence-based wellness initiatives, the "Research" directory includes folders related to academic studies, user feedback and metrics tracking.

Health Gamification Studies: The Health Gamification Studies subfolder houses research pepers, articles and studies related to the effectiveness of health gamification. This academic literature provides valuable insights into the impact of wellness games on user behavior and health outcomes.

User Feedback: Collecting user feedback is essential for continuous improvement. The User Feedback subfolder documents feedback received from users, including suggestions, testimonials and reviews. Analysing this information helps developers understand user needs and preferences.

Wellness Metrics: The Wellness Metrics subfolder is dedicated to tracking and analysing metrics related to the impact of wellness games on users' well-being. This includes quantitive data such as user engagement, retention rates and qualitative data gathered through surveys or interviews.
